  "text": "Found 3 Java source files containing ACL authorization logic in apache/kafka under the clients/src/main/ directory. No relevant files were found in core/src/main/. The files define core ACL authorization interfaces and exceptions: (1) Authorizer.java defines the main Authorizer interface extending Configurable and Closeable, which is the pluggable authorizer interface for Kafka brokers. It includes methods for authorization (authorize), ACL management (createAcls, deleteAcls), and ACL querying (acls). (2) AuthorizerServerInfo.java defines an interface providing runtime broker configuration metadata to authorizers during startup, including cluster resource, broker id, endpoints, and listener information. (3) AuthorizerNotReadyException.java defines a RetriableException class indicating that the authorizer is not ready to receive requests yet. These core interfaces and exception classes form the foundation of Kafka's pluggable authorization framework."
